<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>Which economic reform of the Progressive Era had the MOST lasting impact?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">The Federal Reserve System</option>
            <option letter="b">The Federal Trade Commission</option>
            <option letter="c">The Clayton Antitrust Act</option>
            <option letter="d">The Federal Income Tax</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The creation of the Federal Reserve System in 1913 fundamentally transformed the American financial system by establishing central control over monetary policy and banking. While the FTC regulated business practices, the Clayton Act strengthened antitrust enforcement, and the income tax provided government revenue, the Federal Reserve's ability to manage the money supply and prevent banking panics has had the most enduring influence on American economic stability.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
